Now the children at the orphanage at Thare have a thousand dollars which was donated In Memory Of The Men Stationed at Nakhon Phamon Who Never Returned Home.  The field on which our Jolly Green Giant landed in 1969 when we came to help the orphanage during the Vietnam War has been planted with American Wild Flowers by the children to remember the GI's.<br><br>
Thanks to the former members of the 56th Special Operations <br>
Wing at Nakhon Phanom and the families of those who were killed or remain missing in helping me raise this money.  You have made a difference today for the future tomorrow.<br><br>
We are planning to have a reunion of men who were stationed at NKP during the war, and also hope to continue this donation yearly.  Peace to you
